title: The Westin Hilton Head Island Resort & Spa
text: What can I do?  Oh well.....  It was a nice resort until 3 days ago.  They were raising room rates by 100%, adding fees on top of fees, charging 15.00 a day resort fee, adding fees for valet when you self park and valet is 1:00 ~1:30 extra a day.  Up until today you could self park for $10.00 a day, self park and valet is $20.00. You cannot get any additional incentives like the horseback riding or even a late check out!!!!!  The room wait time at the hotel has increased 2~ 4 hrs on just following the dress code!!!!  They have added all these fees and have basically nothing left!!!  NOT FAIR!  Of course the supervisors think their ok to leave their post and go play pool, sit around and do nothing. Not doing it!!!!  Except for the following: (put in date, got a good tip)  Housekeeping,
name: Lynda Little

title: Crowne Plaza Shenandoah - Woodlands Area, an IHG Hotel
text: Very nice hotel on us highway 90 headed north. Full service restaurant. Comfortable beds and up to date modern hot tubs in the fitness center. This hotel is large casino, with a ski lift and lots of nice corords for enjoying the cold air in your down coat.
name: Lewis Bishop

title: Addis Restaurant
text: Addis has the most delicious Ethiopian food. We love the beef zil zil tibs and the stews. Everything we've tried has been delicious. You can add veggies to any dish. So tasty and the friendliest service.
name: Emily Castle

title: PUMP Restaurant Lounge
text:
Meals were good and really liked the seasonal dishes.
The steak was not as good as I expected, there’s little fat, not enough flavor and didn’t try to it, my husband said it was almost done.
Mediterranean salad was really good.
Brussel sprouts and mashed potatoes were ok, would try something else next time.
Apple pie is pretty good, wife liked it.
Shrimp cocktail could be better for the price, not much for $24. Solid dessert options.
Place is spacious and has neat decoration, crowd was picking up during the evening.
Weird was the separated facilities for men and women, I don’t know why they can’t put everyone in the same restrooms. Review from our Linked In
https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn%3Ali%3Aaction%3Adjournandpublish%3Ast%3A15632
name: Linda Cooke

title: Frankie's of Charlotte
text: Fun place love the neon lights while bowling.  Kids had fun.  How ever I think when you pay 40.00 and hour to bowl you should be able to bowl an hour.  We played 1 game and only took us 30 minutes.  Yet we could only play one game.  Little pricy.
name: Rhonda Jones

title: Holiday Inn Express & Suites Swift Current, an IHG Hotel
text: Friendly staff, but had issues charging the company card that was pre authorized the day before. On checkout day, there was no hot water for a shower or bath after rubbing the water for 7 minutes. Not going to waste any more time or water to see if there warm water behind it eventually. Nice looking rooms and comfortable beds though.
name: PorscheRacer14

title: Golden Green Hotel Daily & Extended Stay - Loving Hut Vegan Restaurant
text:
There are some reviews on here for the old steakhouse in Milwaukee that just say what a great expeirence it was so I will try to do likewise this old Roadhouse/Mussels restaraunt.

It’s located just off of I-90 on highway 175 in Port Edwards. The view from the parking lot is of the river and bridge.

We arrived around 12:30 pm on a Sunday afternoon. It was about 75-80 degrees out and everything looked nice and green and pretty. When we walked in we were greeted by the gentleman who worked the front desk(he also waited tables and so did the manager), the lady in the gift shop and her co-worker. Everyone was smiling and welcoming. We also saw a glimpse of the gentleman who worked the fryolators. It looks like they have some employees with lots of experience working here! A lot of old-school waitstaff is shown only the best.

I ordered the pulled
name: Angela Hughes

title: Vallarta's Mexican Restaurant
text: This place is wonderful affordable  and delish
name: Clifford Richards

title: Cinemark 20 and XD
text: Great movie theater with very comfy seating. Their food is more expensive than other places in the area, but their food is always really good and comes out hot. Ice cream is right outside the theater neat the wall windows.
name: Angela Storey

title: Addis Restaurant
text: The experience was very good great hospitality great food
name: Jenna Graham

title: PUMP Restaurant Lounge
text:
Brunch!!!!!!! Looooooove the Eggs Benedict.
Espresso Martinis are ON point as are all their cocktails I’ve had. Waiters always seem to be sharp and attentive when we visit. The outdoor so-cal dining vibe is really chill and fun.
name: Mark B

title: Lalibela Ethiopian Restaurant
text: The platter was quite delicious & filling that I ended up having leftovers to go. This spot is worth visiting & I look fwd to the day when the live music will be back though that which was playing still helped to warm up the socially-distanced setup.
name: Laura Saint Jean

title: Cinemark 20 and XD
text: the guy at the main entrance was racist and rude he had a attitude and was looking down my shirt i am young teen and this made me very uncomfortable as a person i'm not coming back EVER!!!!
name: ducky sucky

title: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
text: The sushi was really good, as it should be. They also had other things like cheesecake and watermelon. They had a robot bring you the drinks you ordered. Every 15 plates you eat you get a prize. Between me, my brother, and my dad we each had a prize. I was fighting for my life on the way to the car and on the way home I was so full. It was a wonderful evening and I would 10/10 recommend it.
name: Alana Reddy

title: Quality Inn & Suites
text: I do not recommend the worst hotel that could exist because it does not have hygiene or cleanliness the horrible rooms with the stench of cigarettes and marijuana is not recommended for anyone or children the bathrooms in poor condition and the bed sheets torn the dirty curtains fatal everything  very bad horrible
name: Rocio Cumberbatch

title: Vallarta's Mexican Restaurant
text: Great food and people!
name: Keturah Martin

title: El Sombrero Mexican Restaurant
text: El Sombrero has always been a staple in the Northland. Always packed, Always quick service and Always Great Food !
name: Douglas Edgar

title: Golden Green Hotel Daily & Extended Stay - Loving Hut Vegan Restaurant
text: Great hotel! Everything was clean, safe and in prised order, as well as updated decor throughout the hotel. Room was very clean with a cool feature. Ice water dispensed from the headboard would be my only gripe about the stay. The double beds where perfect sizes for a couple. The desk chair was a standard chair that you find in most local restaurants, which was a little disappointing. Wifi is provided by the hotel but they use a bandwidth monitoring software called Sandbox which blocks encrypted sites and websites with login prompts. The intent is to trap and remove phishing pages, but common services (Cloudflare, DuckDuckGo, and HackerSafe) aren't whitelisted. The hotel desk will help with bypassing the software for your logins but it comes at a price. I'm sure it's for the greater good, putting your mind at ease, but I felt a little nagged that i wasn't accessing everything I needed.  The outdoor pool area
name: Alison Morris

title: Round 1
text: Wonderful arcade!! We love visiting here. HUGE arcade with some of the best games available! Everything from pinball to bowling. They offer some of the best fun we have had in NM. Very affordable for the amount of options . The prize room has some great options and we have always left with a smile on our faces. It is also very convenient to just about every store and restaurant you could think of. This is a must try if your in the area!
name: Josh S

title: Hampton Inn & Suites Orange Beach/Gulf Front
text: The breakfast fair at the Golden Parlor include the usual, if slightly over cooked, sausage and fried bland potatoes. There were also muffins and danishes on the table. The  daily newspaper is located by the entrance to the buffet area. In keeping with the times the valet parking service refused to park only one vehicle in my party and demanded an extra fee of 15%. @20$ per night the hotel charges 3$ for WiFi pic that you have to watch for each time you log onto your page.
name: Gerald O'Connor

title: PUMP Restaurant Lounge
text: I've been here 3 times and it's been awesome. Their steaks are cooked perfectly. They gave me 5 ounce filet as a Valentine's Day gift to me instead of charging me for 20 ounce steak. It was perfect.
name: Dorothy Shaw

title: Jaegers Subsurface Paintball
text: Great field, staff, and owners. Breakfast club on Sunday mornings is where it's if you're a tournament player.
name: Kenney Phillips

title: The LINE LA
text: My hotel of choice when I'm in LA. I was surprised that Commissary was gone, but the current restaurant Openaire was excellent for dinner. Staff is always super friendly and I love the minimalist rooms. Always sleep well here. X
name: Jessica Zapotechne

title: Hungry Howie's Pizza
text:
Ordered and Paid online for Brixx to deliver for our Bucknell get together. I ordered the pepperoni calzone and a pepperoni stromboli slices for 4 people
Order was delivered fairly quickly and our server was very nice. We each took the remaining calizone and stromboli home for lunch.
FOOD:
Calizone was huge! I was able to cut it into 5 pieces. The crust was nice and airy and had a good garlic, salt and butter taste. There was a ton of cheese inside with about 6 pepperonis. Also stuffed with spinach. We each loved this calzone; it's made with love and taste delicious.
The stromboli slices were just right when heated. I like that the cheese is optional on stromboli slices. Those slices will make a nice lunch!
TOTAL COST:  $32.89 NOT including tip
TOTAL SERVED: 10
(there were 10
name: Declan Collins

title: Best Western Colorado River Inn
text: Filming location of "YAMASHITA TOMOHISA ROUTE66" document in 2012
name: オルヤンORUYAN

title: Best Western Colorado River Inn
text: Awesome hotel. Clean & very nice rooms! Beds were comfortable too!! Denise at the front desk was a complete pleasure to talk to. We will definitely be back.
name: My Best Life

title: PUMP Restaurant Lounge
text: Good food, nice atmosphere
name: Alex Jones

title: The Westin Hilton Head Island Resort & Spa
text: The hotel wasn't too fancy and needed some sprucing up after a remodel but it did the job. The hotel restaurant had a bit of a wait and the food isn't great. I went because it was after a late flight but most places were closed or closed their drive thru at 8:30 pm. It was a good wrap but nothing special
name: Megan Curtis

title: Holiday Inn Express & Suites Swift Current, an IHG Hotel
text: Property is undergoing remodel. However, the room was clean and it was enjoyable.
name: Norman Murphy

title: Hilton Daytona Beach Oceanfront Resort
text: Horrible shower pressure, out of date interior styling. Beds are so so. View is amazing. Balconies do not exist. Sliding glass door that just leads to a rail.
name: David Darby

title: Vallarta's Mexican Restaurant
text: I ordered flautas thinking they're fresh made, nope frozen taquitos is what they served me. The salsa if really good though!
name: Faith Holmes

title: Bridges Bay Resort
text: Good views, lots of room, busy and popular place. And they serve adult beverages at the pool.
name: Elle S

title: El Sombrero Mexican Restaurant
text: Straight from the 1970's decor, but the food is classic Tex-Mex. Salsa was surprisingly good.
name: Mirena Briggs

title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood
text: Such a cute little family owned little Italian place in Northern Indiana. It is located in a old renovated little house(which was very beautiful inside). The food was wonderful! We had the Tortellini Gusto and I loved everything about this dish. It was a bit pricey but it was well worth what you got. The service was fast and the waitress was great! We will be back.
name: Mark Smith

title: Electric Playhouse
text: I had my son's birthday party here & the staff went above and beyond! Sonia, Scott and John were absolutely amazing - from Sonia helping to plan the event from beginning to end, Scott being one of the best server/host and John overlooking the entire production to ensure everything went perfect! The games and food are excellent as well!
name: Sarika Patel

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text: This is the best zoo I've ever been to.  Animals were not cramped and they were all out playing.  They had all sorts of events going, like bubble races & a beach party.  Worth the money!!
name: Tony Edwards

title: Quest Motel
text: Room was clean! Roomy!! End of floating docks were  good for fishing as were the 150 between docks. Close to town. Very professional and helpful staff
name: Abbie Adams

title: Hampton Inn & Suites Orange Beach/Gulf Front
text: 🤮🤮🤮 will never go back
name: Deanthony Stepter

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text: Good full service hotel.  The property is older but well maintained.  Very good service.
name: Michael LeGay

title: Golden Green Hotel Daily & Extended Stay - Loving Hut Vegan Restaurant
text: LAX is a terrible airport to come through but with this Hilton right there it's not as bad as it could be. The lobby has lots of comfy couches and quiet. The basic room rate is 67. I will say if you can have a hbo add-on that's a good deal. CAUTION! the upgrades may look good but they will raise the total rate. Like the Honey moon night discount, if you take that take it off rather than add on when doing the booking.
name: Rebecca Barlow

title: Hilton Sandestin Beach Golf Resort & Spa
text:
A little dated and could use a little more variety of restaurants and more local cuisine.
But, great location and views.
Breakfast options are not good, and my Hilton Honors status didn't get me squat outside of choosing a good room.
name: Clay Ogata

title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text: Very authentic german cuisine with a warm and inviting atmosphere. Everything came served piping hot — just the way we like it! The giant pretzel is a must try. Plan on plenty of time dining since it’s very busy during the dinner rush. Side dishes were reasonable at $3 and perfectly portioned to share.
name: Ronald Griffiths

title: Denver Zoo
text: Noah’s Ark is for the adventurer in all of us. Your little ones will love meeting and playing with Snow the polar bear; Rhonda the rhinoceros; Canela the Samoyed and many other dogs, cats and other animals. It’s a great place to rest and have fun in the sun. As an extra bonus, there is also a children’s hospital close by.
name: Mohamed Jones

title: Home grown GA Restaurant
text: Great food, great place and good service.
name: Hannah Hopkins

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Had no idea this place existed 30 min from me. Delicious food. Had the fettuccini Sicilian and it was soooo flavorful, as were the mozzarella sticks. My friend had the meatball pasta and she loved it.
name: Jordan and Enya Crane

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Great selection of popular Italian dishes.  Great area too.
name: DLANE

title: Bowlero Cherry Creek
text: In the line to setup our lane #1 bowlers witnessed some drunk guy bump the scorer in lane #4. Scorer hits her head on the stainless steel. She's lying unconscious on the floor. Things like this happen wayyy more often than someone taking a piss in the urinal. Not happy about this at all
name: Sylvia Peters

title: Free Play Arcade - Richardson
text: As a café, Milk Bar has the most welcoming atmosphere and delicious coffee. While the selection can be limited, the dedication of the staff makes it worth the stop! The arcade is a trendy place for gamers, and the cabinets of arcade games and pinball is plentiful. Definitely worth a stop if you're in town!
name: Andrew Hicks

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Came in for a bite. The food was amazing! Prices, portions and taste are spot on. This is our new go to spot! Sanity is restored!
name: Hazel Bryan

title: El Sombrero Mexican Restaurant
text:
Camzon's is one of the best Mexican experiences I have ever had in my life! My wife isn't into Mexican that much but after this visit she was truly blown away by Camzons as was I many times over, hehe. I thought these pictures would help tell all the other customers anticipating this visit, that we didn't get when eating there...
I ate the Denver omelet and it costed $13 and it was really really good. I have probably never had one better and to have such affordable prices mark this review at 5 stars all the way. I'd say that this review deserves ten stars plus and I am sure most other customers would agree with me on that. It's not a far drive here at all and was close by for me as I live in a neighboring community but I am so happy I found this place and look forward to my next visit with less interuption, such as during the breakkast hour, hehe.
Delish
name: Hannah Bradshaw

title: Electric Playhouse
text:
I haven't been here since I was in highschool. First remember it from that movie with Christian Slater.  Wildwood is a great place to go with your kids.  You win some tickets, if you win a prize you can get it at one of the four discounted store at the train/bus station.
You can play as much as you like.
Lazer Maze, Giant Jumping Ball(strictly for kids),Mini Golf, and the train.
name: Jacqueline Weston

title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text: We were sooooo excited for this place, but the authentic german food just left us feeling like something more to be desired. A little on the unkempt side, a little skeevy, but we tried to stay open minded. We did love sitting outside watching the boats go by! Still bummed its a byob :( no german lagers available, again, just a bummer and we had such high hopes.
name: Charlie Fratz PBB

title: Hampton Inn & Suites Orange Beach/Gulf Front
text: Great food,service,room and all around experience!! Place is first class!!
name: George Holloway

title: First Western Inn Caseyville
text: Room was clean but they had cockroaches that was gross didn't know until our second night cause they was in the bathroom
name: Christina Stacey

title: J. Alexander's Restaurant (Overland Park Grill)
text: Super impressed by the quality of the food and service here. Let's talk about the service. Staff was on point and gave me recommendations beyond the classic burger. I had the BSE, it was cooked perfectly and tasted amazing. The sides came in super helpful sizes to replenish the emptiness in your stomach post burger. Also impressed with their recycling system. Would definitely keep doing this and come back to order their perfect medium rare again!
name: Gareth Brown

title: Quest Motel
text: Very clean basic motel. Owners were really nice and helpful  Beds are very comfy and got a good night's sleep. Can hear the train whistle which brought back childhood memories
name: Lois K

title: J. Alexander's Restaurant (Overland Park Grill)
text: Very warm and luxe atmosphere. High quality ingredients. Great service. We had Calamari, Grilled Pork Tenderloin, Rattlesnake Pasta, and Signature Salad. The Thai Bang Bang sauce on the pork blew my mind!
name: Mckenzie Schmitz

title: Vallarta's Mexican Restaurant
text: Have been here multiple times with average experiences, this last time, however, sealed the deal for me. Ordered a lunch special and got 1, ONE! tamale (or enchilada, whatever). One? Really? We ordered take out so I called back & was told, 'yep, you get one!' But that's not what the menu said; silly me.
name: colleen branson

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Amazing Risotto!  I have come to expect Italian Food to be pedestrian like Olive Garden. What I found was a local place that completely blew me away. Comparing Frank's to Olive Garden is like comparing a Five Guys hamburger to a Big Mac. There simply is no comparison: this food is awesome!
name: Ed Tolliver

title: Sky Zone Trampoline Park
text: Definitely worth the trip!  Lots of fun and great party rooms.  Swim lessons available here too.
name: Harriet Bradley

title: Hotel Bel-Air
text: Definitely not up to dorchester standards. The hotel is nice. I got really disappointed because we booked a suite for 10 days then left and booked the same suite when I came back for another few days. The first suite was extremely tiny it would even be considered small for a room. On the other hand when I came back and booked the same variety they gave me what was supposed to be a suite. Which is triple the size of the first one. The first one was also very far from the lobby a good 10 minute walk on the other hand the second suite we got was very close to the lobby. Extremely disappointing for a dorchester hotel
name: Muneera Abdulmohsen

title: Electric Playhouse
text:
Came here for the first time for yoga- I will come back!
Super cool environment!
Staff was friendly.
name: Alycia Lee

title: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
text: This place is so awesome! We were late for our play, and this just happened to be right across the street. VERY FUN! Me and my fiance are definitely going to go back.
name: Don McCall

title: Golden Green Hotel Daily & Extended Stay - Loving Hut Vegan Restaurant
text: Very nice hotel vegan friendly
name: Douglas Green

title: Honeycomb Bed & Breakfast
text: Beautiful property, rooms in the "bungalow" are very nice with one 1 queen and two twins in a bedroom with a full kitchen. Bathroom is attached to bedroom, with a tub and shower. Outhouse is located directly across from building. Fire pit is located across from buildings in field. Lot’s of windows to look out and see the beautiful landscape. Breakfast in a basket is served on a dark, green tray: Biscuits, sausage, fruit, and a muffin. Very good food, however, I wish the couple would use some other type of plate other than the tray for serving their dish. The plate causes the nicer looking tupperware to get messed up through the week. I would consider staying here again.
name: Vanessa Dunn

title: Paulo and Bill Restaurant
text: A hidden gem and a fantastic experience! I highly recommend Wild West if you're looking for a great Italian meal. The restaurant has a welcoming atmosphere, with authentic, quality food that won't break your bank account. The staff was friendly and placed orders at a good pace. A great experience overall!!
name: Glen Lynch

title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood
text:
We had a family gathering of seven and a baby and asked for a reservation at 5:30. It seemed odd that it took a managers approval to make the reservation, but when we arrived, they ushered us into a lovely glassed in semi-private room. This was delightful! But the service and the staff exceeded everyone’s expectations, and then the food arrived! Wow!
We recommend Plate Restaurant in Leawood and will be back regularly, not just for special events.
name: Gerould Sabin

title: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
text: I take my kids here every  weekend and we love it. Has a variety of food choices and dishes. They have a great team here and it’s clean every time.
name: Anne Scott

title: Golden Green Hotel Daily & Extended Stay - Loving Hut Vegan Restaurant
text: The worst hotel ever in my life, unclean dirty ugh paid 80$
name: i Mhageer

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text: Great museum! They have a planetarium, hiking trails, they'll pick you up when you get lost, a cafe, and the history of dinosaurs is so well put together. I was genuinely impressed. If you like dinosaurs, you'll love this place. It'd be really cool if they had some airplanes hanging from the ceiling like some other museums have. The collection could use an update as well- I'd love to see some new baby dinosaurs (no parasaurs tho 🤦‽🤦‍♀️) and some government issued models of the creatures too. The gift shop is ridiculously nice and I would've loved to spend a couple hours in there but I also had little kids with me lol. This should go here as a museum subject and not a comment on the actual museum. Thank you for the hospitality, it is appreciated.
name: Caroline Brown

title: Marhaba Grill
text: Love love love the food. What an incredible price for all you can eat food. Lamb shank was just perfect. Fish was fall off the bone. Spices were just incredible. Place is not super pretty and ambiance is nonexistent but go for the incredible dishes.  I am still giving it a 5 star and coming back every time I am in the cities.
name: Jade Fang

title: Bridges Bay Resort
text: Loved our stay, can't wait to go back!
name: Anna Dale

title: Hotel Bel-Air
text: Enjoy staying here... The room, the bed, everything was very clean and the staff was professional, polite and friendly. I do recommend!!
name: Joanna Mitchell

title: Sky Zone Trampoline Park
text: Place falling apart and dirty. Leaks everywhere, stair handle extremely loose, dusty and limited staff. I know Van Nuys site has staff members at each center making sure everyone is safe, this location has doesn’t. Kids are climbing where they are not supposed to. Big kids kicking little kids out of the basketball area and not letting them play. I’m surprised for such as key location they have not kept up with the place the way they should. Try Van nuys or Thousand Oaks location.
name: Inga Gomez

title: Best Western Colorado River Inn
text: Employees are nice. Working  4am to 2pm. Came back to the room at 1:30pm on a Thursday & our room still wasn't clean. No worries,  it's not like I'm a slob. Went to the housekeeping cart & called out into a room I assumed was being cleaned & nobody answered or was in the room. I put my dirty towels in the bag hanging off the cart & grabbed clean ones & was good to go. No worries.  Put a do not disturb on my door & all was well. My complaint is that there were so many flies in my room when I arrived on the day before. I used a hand towel & killed them all. The a/c filters were filled with lint, like a clothes dryer filter. (The pictures I'm showing here are AFTER I cleaned them). I pulled them out & banged them together outside my door & the lint flew off into the wind. Then I rinsed them off in the shower & dried them & put them back. No worries 👍 sneezing problem solved. Also had to use a hand towl in room 114 to slam in the bottom of the entry door where critters could crawl in from outside.  The insulation on the bottom right corner of the door was missing.  Showerhead had bad water pressure due to corrosion as well & several outlets in the room didn't work. Other than that the place isn't that bad. I'll return for work but bring a flyswatter & clean the a/c filters in the room with each visit.
name: Vikki Horchar

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text: Great place to stop and stretch.
name: Vincent Smith

title: RODEO MEXICAN RESTAURANT
text: Rodeo Mexican Restaurant is the best Mexican restaurant in the entire KC area. Better than anything on Southwest Blvd or any other popular place. Their food is creative and perfectly delicious every time. You need to come to Basehor just to go here.
name: Mark Reiter

title: Trevino's Mexican Restaurant
text:
Excellent service from this family owned and operated restaurant.
Food was great and I had plenty burrito left to take home. I'll be back
name: dylan fiske

title: Golden Green Hotel Daily & Extended Stay - Loving Hut Vegan Restaurant
text: Room is nice.  Bathroom is inadequate.  Big sink.  Big toliet.  Small shower.  Over the toilet closet is under the sink.  Under the sink the doors open opposite of each other tip over.  Under the sink plumbing is exposed.
name: Conor Ahmed

title: Historic Route 66 Motel
text: Section of a post from the 1900 Transcontinental Railroad route from Selma, Calif. to Astoria, Ore. due to the sheer unlikeability for the fare. This post, written on May 6th, 1901 in Selma, Calif, explains the other side of this section's route post. It also describes one aspect of the train itself: a Great American, Pacific Woods (See my pictures below). This aspect of the Rockies/Cascadium National Park shines with explaining in vivid detail how much better the train was than a ship at the time. (the ship was believed to be best at that time, but ships were far more expensive and  extremely realky got rocked. They could view the pass this way and the Rockies were described best this way by even the train riders eyes.)
name: Leslie Johnson

title: Lalibela Ethiopian Restaurant
text: This was our first time trying Ethiopian cousine and we absolutely loved it. Granted, we have nothing to compare it to and I personally can't comment on authenticity. However the overall quality of food, the spices, the freshness and the flavors were amazing.
name: Serg Chernata

title: Trevino's Mexican Restaurant
text: If tacos, nachos, burritos and drinks are what you are looking for then its the place to go!
name: Patricia French

title: Hilton Daytona Beach Oceanfront Resort
text: The hotel is beautiful but the staff really turned it around. A friend who was with me was accusing a staff member of racist behavior but another guest came in and blew up my friend. I was very pleased with how this was handled. The manager was very understanding and I appreciated how quickly the matter was taken care of.
name: Shaun Robson

title: Round 1
text:
This place was pretty chill. Reminded me of that place called Main Event--without the laser tag. Didn't have any bike racks so we had to get creative locking our bikes together around the big pillar outside(see picture). Prices aren't too bad, wish they had specials for certain nights. Love that they serve pitchers! They had Santa Fe's 7K on tap too. Paul and Dinh(sp?) were really cool too.

The downside to the place is that it kinda felt like we were being chaperoned at a field trip or something. Lots of people just watching us... Kinda creepy and unnecessary.
name: R Glenn

title: Home grown GA Restaurant
text: Okay, getting better Veal Cutlet, the salad bar was fantastic! Deserts are delish! Had to make reservations for a Fri.Night, 4 months ahead of time!
name: Stephen Wells

title: Electric Playhouse
text:
When our kids wanted to go, we decided that a 3-hour visit would be best. My kids LOVED the Ninja Castle and had a fantastic, fun time. I was pretty relieved they were interested in something and so shocked they were willing to play together so much.

After walking around, my kids were really tired and needed a nap. For the first time in a long time, they were in bed before 8 pm! Was it the ZooTique? Best visit ever! End Note: they were all bouncing off the wall with energy when they got home.
name: Jill Morgan

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text: Could have been better. Walking up to the hotel to check-in and seeing an overflowing trash can wasn't appealing (see photo). The room was decent, but didn't like seeing someone else's hair on the toilet or in the shower. Cleanliness is an issue that should be improved. The customer service was good though.
name: Jerry

title: The LINE LA
text:
Always a great stay! Beautiful atmosphere great location!!
Check out my IG for more pics @herr_majesty & @travelbae4ever
name: Jerica T

title: Hampton Inn & Suites Orange Beach/Gulf Front
text: Great hotel and casino. Plenty of good restaurants and bars on site with two good butcher shops. Starbucks, CiCi's pizza, Mama Fu's make good food. The buffet is good as well, as well as the noodle dog place on site. I love the old train but took a taxi to the last stop because you really need more than one hour to go through. Very expensive so wear your best walking shoes. It's about a 10-15 minute walk to the little shops, restaurants and bars. Also, make sure you ask for a low floor when you often see the train from your window or it blocks the view. The rooms were clean and nice. I would definitely come back.

title: Wyndham Garden Cross Lanes Charleston
text:
We stopped at a quick one night stop to get some sleep, shower, and back get on the road. It was on the way to where we were headed, so it worked perfectly. Things that need improvement: 1. The thermostat. It was not accurate and as you can see my thermostat said it was 65% humidity, because theirs wasn’t working and wouldn’t trigger air on its own. My husband continued to smell mildew every time he walked into the room, I must have missed it the 2 times I walked in. 2. The vent, it could use some cleaning. I am not sure how clean the air we manually forced out of it was.
Good things on why I scored it high: 1. Price was great. 2. Location for us was awesome. 3. It did the job provide a nice firm mattress for us to get some good shut eye. The pillows could have been comfier, but for the price I will not complain! 4. The one person we interacted with at the desk was great. 5. Had a pool, we didn’t use it but I heard kids were enjoying it when I was checking in. 6. Overall thought things were relatively clean! 7. The bathroom was super cute and had a cool mirror/light. 8. There was a tv, but we didn’t use it. It was small for some standards, but I didn’t care as we were actually just using it for sleep.

If you are looking for a quick stop to get some good sleep and this is on the way, would 100% recommend. If you are looking for a fancier vacation hotel I would probably look elsewhere, but I’m not sure if that’s the area for fancier hotels.
name: Jacqueline Hartman

title: Ray’s Splash Planet
text:
Save your money and time; go to Ray’s Splash Planet. Great Wolf is always sold out and expensive. Thank me in advance.—CC
Clean facility(They have locker rooms, brink a lock, or carry a tot for your towels; Excellent Customer Service. No food allowed, so keep your cooler in the car to snack, but you can come back in without a hassle. The only thing is parking fills up quickly, but overall pleasure and very affordable experience. Enjoy!

title: Chicago Getaway Hostel
text:
I stayed in this hostel for almost two months just off-and-on. The hostel is quite large and one can often find as much, if not more, peace and quiet there than in an apartment. The majority of the kitchen's storage and dishes are at Taylor Apartment next door, but the café-style drink area and good deal of outdoor seating can be beneficial.

The venue is known primarily as a place for partying and many do or have at some point but that doesn't have to ruin it for the rest of us. There are a good number of quite friendly and helpful staff who lessen the severity of mistake which could get you a "boot" (permanent removal). It is a hostel after all. I once left my laptop three weeks and returned to find it safe and sound by the staff behind the desk. The place is clean overall and even after many years bit of wear and tear can be seen; but the wifi was always very fast and reliable
name: Patrick Tomlinson

title: RODEO MEXICAN RESTAURANT
text:
Its a small place that you could easily pass it by I mistook it for a house.
It's a place to go if you have a craving for mexican food and your in a pinch.
It was busy at lunch on a monday and the food was not quick get but it was well worth the wait.
I got two tacos and the house special for a total of $15.
I'd definitely go back if i'm ever in the area.

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City

title: Breakout KC Escape Room | River Market
text: 5 stars all the way!! The energy of this place is just so much fun. As soon as you walk in you feel like you’ve been transported to another magical world! The staff here is a dream. They’re super friendly and great with kids! They even made a point to make sure we were aware that they offer a family membership. They say they’re a magical world without the price of a flight, but they're a world that takes you away from just about anything else too! We had an absolutely magical time here and I couldn’t recommend it more! You can tell they put a lot of thought and love into the design of this place and it makes for the perfect escape! Go for a kids party! Come for a couples date! Completely worthy of everyone of your minutes here. I guarantee that you and your family and friends will love it as much as we did. 🧞‍♂️

With a driving range and actual golf course at the same location, Smiley's has something for everyone!

text:
Had an awesome experience. The first room we received was kinda hot, with the vent on the floor so we kept our feet off the floor. After a little over an hour, we go them to change our room because of the air vent. They were extremely helpful and accommodating. The bellman helped us pack everything in our car and they were so kind! We liked them so much we stayed another night! We got a fridge and microwave in this room! Shower was clean, water was nice and hot! Bed was so comfy and room was huge with the fridge and microwave!  ATM and other conventisment store ub the first floor. The fun zone is two hours. Always fun!!❤️

Also, the sky top cafe has amazing food. I had breakfast there and it was incredible. You get a beautiful view without leaving the hotel. I split a raspberry truffle crepe with my friend and it was better than I could ask for. Sweet and savory

title: Round 1

title: Ray’s Splash Planet
text: I took a gamble and commuted over an hour to visit here with my son and his buddy today after researching and finding Ray's Splash Planet online. This facility far exceeded my expectations. The dressing rooms and facility itself was clean and updated. It was $35 for all three of us (out of city residents) to swim/play all day which isn't even one ticket at other water parks. We have been to our fair share of water parks, splash pads, etc. and I have never experienced lifeguards and staff remain so continuously attentive and alert in their positions. Not once did I see a lifeguard distracted by their cell phones, talking to each other, nothing of the sort. I noticed the staff rotated positions frequently, took safety checks in their zones, and were quick to act in situations to prevent accidents or injury. As a parent, I value and appreciate these proactive practices so much. I would definitely recommend this place and will return in the future.
name: Savannah Johnson

title: Kura Revolving Sushi Bar
text: Requested a table and willing to wait for it, did not get one. Requested two waters, got one. No alcohol. The stuffing of the blue crab California roll, the rainbow roll, and the caterpillar roll tasted like over mayoed coleslaw. They obviously use the same odd filling for several rolls, and it is all you taste. We sat right next to kitchen and heard the chefs talking about peeing and pooping for like 3 minutes straight. Also if you fill out the survey at the end, the chefs and servers get it immediately, as they instantaneously mentioned that they got a poor review. So that was super awkward.

title: Denver Zoo
text:
Quite small, but good enough for a quick visit with the kiddos. This place has a giraffe feeder where you can take pellets right up to them to feed. They are friendly and will come right up to your window to feed. There was a cutesy petting zoo and mini train out front. The petting zoo was nice tho a little limited on the animals. A couple of goats, bunnies, ducks and a chicken. The train is extra $3.95, but cute for the kiddos.
Strollers are $10.00 and regular entrance is $12.00.
name: Aimee Gallagher

title: Electric Playhouse
text: A very interesting form of entertainment here I must say. So you enter a brightly lit room to pay for entry….and then you go into a tunnel of neon lights and immediately are submerged into a neon maze of fun! There are several different activities to enjoy along with a drink station and bar. My son and I went and paid $18 a ticket for a pass for a few hours. Some of the games where really fun and interactive well others where kind of meh. The dodgeball space invader game and the larger than life breakout game where are favorites. The only downsides are it does get crowded and kind of smelly…I mean there’s lots of kids running around sweating 😅 also there isn’t that much to do considering majority of the main events get completed fairly quickly. We where kind of over it after an hour due to all the screaming kids but the initial wow factor is great. We decided to hit the snack bar and I was hoping for an adult beverage but no one would help us. The staff was in the kitchen dancing and the bartender only seemed interested in helping a certain group of people at the bar. So we left, I don’t think we will go back but it’s definitely something everyone should go try once
name: Crystal Bean

text: First time at Hilton Resort, had a wonderful time, great customer service from valet, front desk, housekeeping,and gift shop.Great food and service at Don Rico's Bar and Grill. title: The LINE LA
text:
After we checked in, the first room assigned for us was full of the smell of weed, and the doorman who helped us with luggages said he felt the same thing. The second room assign for us was better, we thought. But, there was a "boxed water" with only half inside. Have no idea whether it was served by the hotel or left by the previous customer. BUT it is only half bottle. Then when we woke up this morning, we figured out there is a stain on the comforter. We suspected it was a blood stain. Then we found the hotel manager, he kept saying that everything has been washed and he could guarantee that this is clean.

It is not only the quality of this hotel. We could bear the mistakes. BUT the attitude of the manager and the front desk was disgusting. In their thoughts, once we reached the supervisor, the problem should have been finished, even we were not OK with their solutions. And they also said so when we tried to reach out the supervisor again since we are not satisfied with the solution, like “you have already met my supervisor, and this problem now should have been solved. Sorry but I cannot let you see my supervisor again. “

Hotel is on the outside of the city, but the main road is connecting the exit/entrance on it. The rooms are clean, with A/C and 2 flat screen TVs. Well, overall it is a very good hotel.

Fajita’s meat was very dry and hard, had to break it with our teeth. But by the time he took they plate, they offered me a new one which saved me from embarrassment. I hope he’ll remember this perfection. Overall it was 5 star experience for me. I would recommend others for coffee drinks.

title: Harrah's Cherokee Valley River
text: Typical Vegas hotel. A bunch of shops, restaurants and bars downstairs and what felt like a block of nightclubs. We tried the buffet on Saturday which had a huge variety of foods but the quality was just so meh. It was like eating semi-cold cafeteria food. I didn't notice if there were shuttles to other resorts so we took the Deuce on Sunday. We ate at two restaurants on the strip, first was Maghann the Italian place and I found the Lamb Ragu to be oven roasted and fallen off the bone soft. Definitely will be a restaurant I go back to if New York ever opens up, kinda like I posted about in a review about John Jaspers Place when it was still in LA. We went to CUT, Steak House and had a whole lobster. The lobster was interesting because you got the claws, the meat and the delicious tomalley which is basically the liver of the lobster. I definitely think it was delicious and if this was
name: Gavin Jones

title: Hinkle Fun Center
text: Took our 14 y.o. niece and everyone, including adults, had a great time.  Staff was excellent.  The unlimited pass is you best value but allow several hours to accommodate the activities.
name: Edward Ayoub

title: PUMP Restaurant Lounge
text: Very delicious food and knowledgeable staff. Great atmosphere with a lovely patio.
name: Tina Davies

title: Bridges Bay Resort
text: This was a pretty decent place. It has a lot to offer. The staff was absolutely spectacular. The lakefront property is excellent. The hotel has a great feel to it. There are a few maintenance items and cleaning items that need to be done. A carpet shampooer would do wonders on the level 1 hallway. But for the most part, it is a pretty nice place with some excellent people.
name: Chad Chapman

title: J. Alexander's Restaurant (Overland Park Grill)
text: The food was outstanding. The service was just okay. Our server did not give us very much attention. This was partly due to the restaurant being busy, but I was surprised to not be asked if I wanted a second drink. Overall, an enjoyable meal though.
name: Ryan Mattison

title: Wendy's
text: I guess this is why the Jr. Cheeseburgers are less expensive there's no meat.  How? This thing has 4 ingredients how do you forget the patty lmao.  12/27/21 at 12:01 pm.
name: mat M

title: Trap Music Museum
text: I definitely expected way more. This museum has so much potential to be better. I think things needs space. Everything just seems to be on top of each other. The bar definitely takes up too much space and should be at the beginning so people can walk with drinks. It being at the end after taking pics and being hot just wasn’t it for me. The best part was my daughter meeting TI daughter and her being so nice and friendly to take a picture with her. ❤️
name: Katherine Allotta

title: Addis Restaurant
text: Awesome vegetarian options!! All the food is freshly cooked, yummy and cheap. Staff is very friendly and helpful. The vegetarian platter is my favorite!
name: Leon Fisher

title: Frank's of Parkville
text:
A hidden gem on Franklin St! A true delight!

The service was fast, our waiter was polite and loved the history in the house. The martini's were delicious as well as the tiramisu! Plus it's all in walking distance to everywhere else on the street! Highly recommend! Helpful (0)

Best Italian food in town!
name: Jeffrey Buckley

title: Denver Zoo
text: After living here for 20 years, got to go to my first Denver zoo lights what a fantastic voyage of sight and vision and just beauty of color!
name: Duncan Foss

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text: My 3 year old did enjoy his time here. I’m not sure about kids older than say 7-8. It wasn’t as big as I thought it would be. It’s mostly a linear walkthrough exhibit. Somewhat expensive for the experience. There are some cool interactive pieces.
name: Seán Riley

title: Arabia Steamboat Museum
text: The Steamboat Arabia museum is amazing! The displays and presentation of the recovered artifacts and cargo aboard the ship is very well done; and the preservation work continues still. We briefly met one of the family members of the group of people who sought out finding the vessel and unearthed it. Also, we got to speak with a member of the preservation team, who was working on some shoes. They were very polite and quite passionate about the museum!
name: John Owen

title: Marine Motel
text: Really Awesome stay just love the way my room and everything is set up.
name: Melissa Lee

title: Courtyard by Marriott Kansas City at Briarcliff
text: Overall great experience.  Food was very good in the Red River or Prairie Bistro for dinner and for breakfast in the Frontier Dining Room.  Super friendly and cheerful wait staff.  Hotel is beautifully designed with River stones from the Red River Valley.  Comfortable beds with crisp white linens.  Great view from the dining room.  Excellent complimentary workout room.  Free coffee in lobby from 6-8am.  Amazing dog friendly venue:  48 hour cancellation policy applies to pet friendly rooms. Pets up to 100 lbs are allowed. VALID ALL YEAR
name: Carly Marsh

title: Sky Zone Trampoline Park
text: Best place around for kids. No TVs, no loud noise and most of the time they have a huge box truck that the kids can play in.  Addicting when the kids get the whiff of popping a huge bag of those plastic bears. End up leaving with 50 bears. Huge inflatable obstacle course.  Bowling, huge arcade and fun.  On a few occasions they have a walker train or stroller train if your lil one is scared of big stuff this place is genius for that. Yesterday with sick toddler and lil she needed a little rest was 3 hours and i was feeling super tired by the end. It's so big and fun you forget your tired. Best part no crowds! Jumpers happy face
name: Scott Scott

title: Marhaba Grill
text:
You'll leave here stuffed and happy.
Wish we lived closer... but lived in Maryland. 😉
See—between the 3 of us we ordered 2 salads, 4 meats,

2 sides, 3 rice half a pita.. 1 regular hummus and one with falafel

and 1 iced tea. Best money spent.
name: Tony Smith

title: PUMP Restaurant Lounge
text: Great service excellent food
name: Michael Peters

title: Smiley's Golf Complex
text: Nice and fun to walk, the  girls really enjoyed it and so did we.
name: Kieran Payne

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: Great Chicken Marsala!
name: Shane Ingram

title: First Western Inn Caseyville
text: Stayed in one of the rooms built from converted trailers. The room is cozy but that's all that can be expected from something of this size. They provide robes and slippers in the bathroom and towels in the room. The seats in front of the beds collapse when you pull on a strap on the side, which makes accessing the storage space under easy. Otherwise the amenities are standard for a motel. I don't use them much but these will be helpful in an emergency.
name: Leon Hill

title: Marhaba Grill
text:
Whenever I crave a gyro, this place is where I go to hangout, eat, and buy. I never go wrong every time I come here, food is above and beyond delicious, staff are also great.

The lunch special are a great deal too. It’s a very nostalgic place which reminds me of grandmas cooking in the kitchen and feeding everyone in the family.

I would definitely recommend this place. My only recommendation from visiting around atleast twice a week is to increase the size of the pita pocket your coming with the meat.

Otherwise an amazing place to eat and dine with your family and friends.

The place is also very welcoming and inviting, even when the staff isn’t serving you.
name: Nicole Wright

title: Marriott St. Louis West
text: Clean, nice, good rooms and awesome room amenities, friendly staff
name: Sylvia Phillips

title: El Sombrero Mexican Restaurant
text:
This place seems to have a loyal cult following. Many of the folks sitting in there seem to be friends and family. In fact, one person visiting said he's brought his kid there since she was two. And they live in Smithville which isn't close by.

The chorizo was very tasty. The refried beans are chunky in a good way. We will have to come here again and try their tacos
name: Brian Marsh

title: Free Play Arcade - Richardson
text: Love this place. 12 dollars for all you can play. It can get crowded on tournament nights and weekends but even then there are always some machines available. Best bottle/can beer selection in town!
name: Michelle Brownlee

title: Hotel Bel-Air
text: So beautiful from the stroll outside// to our room the view was so breath taking.. the food in the restaurant was good.. old style cooking for the southern country.. and lovely ambiance!! Thank you so much☺️
name: Kirsty Jones

title: Best of the Wurst German Kitchen
text: Delicious! Reasonably priced and eats a lot!
name: Ellie Bruce

title: Quest Motel
text: This place is wickedddd, good price too
name: Ryan Evans

title: Paulo and Bill Restaurant
text: Tried this place and had the pepperoni pizza. It was delicious! I even got a side of their home made ranch which was also delicious. Also had their raspberry lemonade which was actually a limeade that was not the best. My companions ordered the lasagna, Italian salad and Alfredo with chicken. The salad was good and very fresh. The Alfredo could have used more sauce and more seasoning. The lasagna was okay. They could use a new cheese grater because it got all over us and our waitress was messy and didn't sound that sorry about getting food on us.
name: Lauren Jefferson

title: The Westin Hilton Head Island Resort & Spa
text: Big place, easy to find. Tired hotel that was refurbished a few years ago, nothing modern or eye catching, tired room but essential facilities. Would not purchase again just due to the room condition but experience ok. The room appears to be fridge without a fridge. Disappointing.
name: Geoffrey Booth

title: Breakout KC Escape Room | River Market
text: Can't beat this place for escape rooms in KC.
name: Ryan Gullett

title: SEA LIFE Kansas City
text: Amazing place to hang out with the family.  Lots of fun things to do, even if you are not a thrill seeking person.  Lots of fun in the food area too. The indoor and outdoor zip lines were fun and exciting. The Treetops Adventure was amazing and my 11 year old daughter loved it, even more so than the zip lines. Highly recommend this place.  The workers are very nice and helpful.  Also, it is wheelchair accessible.
name: Joel Moore

title: Quest Motel
text: the room, beds, bathroom, are very clean, the hostress is very nice
name: Frank Cheung

title: Quality Inn & Suites
text:
We were very pleasantly surprised by this beautiful resort on Lake Sammamish. The lakefront rooms open right onto the beach which is a wonderful touch. You can enjoy the garden or just swim!

I had promptly ordered GLUTEN FREE bagels, which ended up as dry scones. Not sure how that happened as they were clearly marked. The strange thing was that the fruit was in a post-processed state. So hard it had to be cut with a knife. Then the strange green glob was guacamole. Scary that this kind of food was just left in the buffet.

Overall the resort was well maintained, the room was nice, though the the deck and lake view were maintained well.

Bugs: it looks like a tropical island and the geckos like the beachness, too. With the green trees, it's a lot more lush than nearby areas. Huge mosquitoes on the patio at night. In the day there are
name: Nigel Saunders

title: Electric Playhouse
text: Very clean and polite staff
name: Eric Rogers

title: Days Inn & Suites by Wyndham Kansas City South
text: It's a fun spot to visit. Great mechanics and oil changes. Short wait.
name: Gerald Owen

title: Addis Restaurant
text: I found this place after my boyfriend was telling me about how much he enjoyed this authentic Ethiopian Resturant that was near OSU campus when he was in college in the early 00s. The food here was amazing. This was a 1st for me and it was so good.  My boyfriend loved the food!!! It was even better than  he remembered. We got the beef chicken mix platter and it was more enough to feed both of us. I also go a coffee ( I will go back just to get a cup togo) and he had a tea ( also amazing)!!
name: Amber Wilson

title: Smiley's Golf Complex
text: Golf and golf and golf. For the price, I like it. They have a nice driving range. Friendly staff. I’ve played the course a few times. The course gets hard in the drier months. They have two mini golfs. One is almost too hard to play, the other is great for families with small kids. It’s a low key place and not many other amenities. If you don’t need frills to golf, check it out.
name: Lee Orrison

title: Historic Route 66 Motel
text: Really great place to spend the night. A mom and pop but very well maintained and very quiet. Two great restaurants in walking distance. Won't disappoint.
name: Randell Hembree

title: Jaegers Subsurface Paintball
text: Huge indoor paintball arena with so many cool games. They have you fill out waiver electronically before going there but rules were not enforced and I saw a lot steel shots made. Apparently there was one minor incident that led to owner being somewhat restrictive/overbearing but overall good arena
name: Amelia Gray

title: Frank's of Parkville
text: We found Franks and had a lovely experience. The atmosphere is quaint and authentic. The sangria was delicious. The meatballs were of a soft texture and appealed not only to the adult fare but also the teenager. The salad dressing was amazing! Both entries were great. The dessert was divine. Let’s talk service - Grace was phenomenal and prompt. Highly encouraged to find this hidden gem.
name: Heidi Johnston

title: Courtyard by Marriott Kansas City at Briarcliff
text: Our second time staying at this property and I don't think we'll look to find another.  Great food, wonderful staff and clean rooms.
name: Ian Morris

title: Free Play Arcade - Richardson
text: So much nostalgia. Found a few random games I've never seen.
name: JaMikal M
